12 9–901.
13 (a) In this subtitle the following words have the meanings indicated.
14 (b) “Active duty” has the meaning stated in 37 U.S.C. § 101.
15 (c) “Active service member” means an individual who is:
16 (1) an active duty member of the uniformed services; or
17 (2) serving in a reserve component of the uniformed services on active duty
18 orders.
19 (d) “Armed forces” has the meaning stated in 10 U.S.C. § 101.
20 (h) “Reserve component” has the meaning stated in 37 U.S.C. § 101.
21 (j) “Service member” means an individual who is a member of:
22 (1) the uniformed services; or
23 (2) a reserve component of the uniformed services.
24 (l) “Uniformed services” has the meaning stated in 37 U.S.C. § 101.
25 SUBTITLE 14A. LICENSING – ACTIVE SERVICE MEMBERS AND SPOUSES.
26 10–14A–01.

SENATE BILL 242 9
1 (A) IN THIS SUBTITLE THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE MEANINGS
2 INDICATED.
3 (B) “ACTIVE SERVICE MEMBER” HAS THE MEANING STATED IN § 9–901 OF
4 THIS ARTICLE.
5 (C) “LICENSE” MEANS A LICENSE, PERMIT, CERTIFICATION,
6 REGISTRATION, OR OTHER LEGAL AUTHORIZATION REQUIRED FOR ENGAGING IN AN
7 OCCUPATION OR A PROFESSION.
8 (D) “LICENSING AUTHORITY” MEANS AN AGENCY OF THE STATE THAT
9 ISSUES A LICENSE.
10 10–14A–02.
11 THIS SUBTITLE DOES NOT APPLY WITH RESPECT TO AN OCCUPATION OR A
12 PROFESSION FOR WHICH AN INDIVIDUAL WHO HOLDS A LICENSE ISSUED IN BY
13 ANOTHER JURISDICTION STATE MAY PRACTICE IN THE STATE UNDER AN
14 INTERSTATE COMPACT.
15 10–14A–03.
16 (A) AN ACTIVE SERVICE MEMBER OR THE SPOUSE OF AN ACTIVE SERVICE
17 MEMBER WHO RELOCATES TO THE STATE BECAUSE OF ORDERS FOR SERVICE AND
18 HOLDS A LICENSE ISSUED BY ANOTHER JURISDICTION STATE MAY PRACTICE IN THE
19 STATE UNDER THE LICENSE FOR THE DURATION OF THE ORDERS IF:
20 (1) THE ACTIVE SERVICE MEMBER OR SPOUSE OF AN ACTIVE SERVICE
21 MEMBER SUBMITS AN APPLICATION TO THE LICENSING AUTHORITY THAT
22 INCLUDES:
23 (I) PROOF OF THE ORDERS;
24 (II) IF THE APPLICANT IS THE SPOUSE OF AN ACTIVE SERVICE
25 MEMBER, A COPY OF THE MARRIAGE CERTIFICATE; AND
26 (III) A NOTARIZED AFFIDAVIT AFFIRMING, UNDER THE PENALTY
27 OF LAW, THAT:
28 1. THE APPLICANT IS THE INDIVIDUAL DESCRIBED AND
29 IDENTIFIED IN THE APPLICATION;

10 SENATE BILL 242
1 2. ALL STATEMENTS MADE IN THE APPLICATION ARE
2 TRUE, CORRECT, AND COMPLETE;
3 3. THE APPLICANT HAS READ AND UNDERSTANDS THE
4 REQUIREMENTS TO RECEIVE A LICENSE AND THE SCOPE OF PRACTICE OF THE
5 STATE;
6 4. THE APPLICANT CERTIFIES THAT THE APPLICANT
7 MEETS AND WILL COMPLY WITH THE REQUIREMENTS AND SCOPE OF PRACTICE
8 DESCRIBED IN ITEM 3 OF THIS ITEM; AND
9 5. THE APPLICANT IS IN GOOD STANDING IN ALL
10 JURISDICTIONS STATES IN WHICH THE APPLICANT HOLDS OR HAS HELD A LICENSE;
11 (2) THE APPLICANT IS IN GOOD STANDING WITH THE REGULATORY
12 AUTHORITY THAT ISSUED THE LICENSE;
13 (3) NO DISCIPLINARY ACTION, INCLUDING REVOCATION, HAS BEEN
14 TAKEN BY A REGULATORY AUTHORITY AGAINST THE APPLICANT REGARDING THE
15 LICENSE;
16 (4) NO INVESTIGATION RELATING TO UNPROFESSIONAL CONDUCT IS
17 PENDING AGAINST THE APPLICANT REGARDING THE LICENSE; AND
18 (5) THE APPLICANT HAS NOT VOLUNTARILY SURRENDERED THE
19 LICENSE WHILE UNDER INVESTIGATION FOR UNPROFESSIONAL CONDUCT BY A
20 REGULATORY AUTHORITY.
21 (B) IF A LICENSING AUTHORITY IS REQUIRED TO CONSIDER WHETHER A
22 LICENSE IS VALID UNDER SUBSECTION (A) OF THIS SECTION BUT CANNOT CARRY
23 OUT THE REQUIREMENT DURING THE 30 DAYS IMMEDIATELY FOLLOWING THE
24 RECEIPT OF THE APPLICATION, THE LICENSING AUTHORITY MAY ISSUE A
25 TEMPORARY LICENSE TO THE APPLICANT THAT CONFERS THE SAME RIGHTS,
26 PRIVILEGES, AND RESPONSIBILITIES AS A PERMANENT LICENSE.
27 (C) A LICENSING AUTHORITY THAT RECEIVES AN APPLICATION SUBMITTED
28 UNDER SUBSECTION (A) OF THIS SECTION MAY CONDUCT A CRIMINAL HISTORY
29 RECORDS CHECK OF THE APPLICANT BEFORE AUTHORIZING THE APPLICANT TO
30 PRACTICE IN THE STATE UNDER SUBSECTION (A) OF THIS SECTION OR ISSUING A
31 TEMPORARY LICENSE TO THE APPLICANT UNDER SUBSECTION (B) OF THIS SECTION.

SENATE BILL 242 11
1 (D) IF AN ACTIVE SERVICE MEMBER OR SPOUSE OF AN ACTIVE SERVICE
2 MEMBER IS AUTHORIZED TO PRACTICE IN THE STATE UNDER SUBSECTION (A) OF
3 THIS SECTION:
4 (1) THE ACTIVE SERVICE MEMBER OR SPOUSE OF AN ACTIVE SERVICE
5 MEMBER MAY PRACTICE UNDER THE LICENSE ONLY IN THE DISCIPLINE AND TO THE
6 EXTENT OF THE SCOPE OF PRACTICE WITHIN WHICH THE LICENSE ALLOWS THE
7 ACTIVE SERVICE MEMBER OR SPOUSE OF AN ACTIVE SERVICE MEMBER TO PRACTICE
8 IN THE OTHER JURISDICTION STATE; AND
9 (2) THE LICENSING AUTHORITY MAY NOT REQUIRE THE ACTIVE
10 SERVICE MEMBER OR SPOUSE OF AN ACTIVE SERVICE MEMBER TO OBTAIN A
11 LICENSE ISSUED BY THE LICENSING AUTHORITY UNLESS THE ACTIVE SERVICE
12 MEMBER OR SPOUSE OF AN ACTIVE SERVICE MEMBER IS SEEKING TO PRACTICE IN A
13 DIFFERENT DISCIPLINE OR WITHIN A DIFFERENT SCOPE OF PRACTICE THAN THAT
14 DESCRIBED IN ITEM (1) OF THIS SUBSECTION.
15 10–14A–04.
16 AN ACTIVE SERVICE MEMBER OR SPOUSE OF AN ACTIVE SERVICE MEMBER
17 THAT IS AUTHORIZED TO PRACTICE UNDER § 10–14A–03 OF THIS SUBTITLE:
18 (1) MAY PRACTICE TO THE SAME EXTENT AND IN THE SAME CAPACITY
19 AS AN INDIVIDUAL LICENSED BY A LICENSING AUTHORITY IN THE STATE,
20 INCLUDING SUPERVISING AN INDIVIDUAL WHO IS LICENSED IN THE STATE WHO IS
21 REQUIRED TO PRACTICE UNDER SUPERVISION; AND
22 (2) IS SUBJECT TO THE SAME DISCIPLINARY AUTHORITY OF A
23 LICENSING AUTHORITY AS AN INDIVIDUAL LICENSED BY THE LICENSING AUTHORITY
24 IN THE STATE.
25 10–14A–05.
26 EACH LICENSING AUTHORITY MAY ADOPT REGULATIONS TO CARRY OUT THIS
27 SUBTITLE.
28 Article – Agriculture
29 1–101.
30 (a) In this article the following words have the meanings indicated.
31 (d) “Department” means the State Department of Agriculture.

12 SENATE BILL 242
1 (i) “Secretary” means Secretary of Agriculture or [his] THE SECRETARY’S
2 designee.
3 2–301.
4 (a) In this subtitle the following words have the meanings indicated.
5 (b) “Board” means the State Board of Veterinary Medical Examiners.
6 (c) “Direct supervision” means that the supervising veterinarian who is licensed
7 and registered in the State OR AUTHORIZED TO PRACTICE VETERINARY MEDICINE IN
8 THE STATE UNDER § 10–14A–03 OF THE STATE GOVERNMENT ARTICLE:
9 (1) Is on the premises of the animal treatment facility;
10 (2) Is available on an immediate basis; and
11 (3) Has given written or oral instructions for treatment of the animal
12 patients involved.
13 (c–1) “Immediate supervision” means the supervising veterinarian who is licensed
14 and registered in the State OR AUTHORIZED TO PRACTICE VETERINARY MEDICINE IN
15 THE STATE UNDER § 10–14A–03 OF THE STATE GOVERNMENT ARTICLE is in the
16 immediate area and within audible and visual range of the animal patient and the person
17 treating the patient.
18 (c–2) “Indirect supervision” means the supervising veterinarian who is licensed and
19 registered in the State OR AUTHORIZED TO PRACTICE VETERINARY MEDICINE IN THE
20 STATE UNDER § 10–14A–03 OF THE STATE GOVERNMENT ARTICLE:
21 (1) Is not required to be in the same facility or in close proximity to the
22 individual being supervised; and
23 (2) (i) Has given written or oral instructions for treatment of the animal
24 patient involved;
25 (ii) Is available to provide supervision by electronic or telephonic
26 means; and
27 (iii) Has arranged for telephonic consultation with a licensed
28 veterinarian, if necessary.
29 (d) “License” means a license to practice veterinary medicine in the State.
30 (i) “Veterinary practitioner” means [a]:

SENATE BILL 242 13
1 (1) A licensed and registered veterinarian engaged in the practice of
2 veterinary medicine; OR
3 (2) AN INDIVIDUAL AUTHORIZED TO PRACTICE VETERINARY
4 MEDICINE IN THE STATE UNDER § 10–14A–03 OF THE STATE GOVERNMENT
5 ARTICLE AND IS ENGAGED IN THE PRACTICE OF VETERINARY MEDICINE.
