31 of small arms ammunition, and up to 5 pounds of black powder for the loading or reloading
32 of small arms ammunition or for use in the loading of antique arms or replicas of antique

92 SENATE BILL 242
1 arms, if the smokeless powder and black powder are stored in their original shipping
2 containers and are possessed only for personal use in firearms.
3 (2) A person may not possess or store explosives for use in firearms in any
4 quantity in multifamily dwellings, apartments, dormitories, hotels, schools, other public
5 buildings, or buildings or structures open for public use.
6 (3) Notwithstanding paragraph (2) of this subsection, the State Fire
7 Marshal may issue a permit to allow temporary possession of explosives for use in firearms
8 in a building or structure open for public use.
