21 Article – Real Property
22 7–105.1.
23 (e) An order to docket or a complaint to foreclose a mortgage or deed of trust on
24 residential property shall:
25 (1) Include:
26 (i) If applicable, the license number of:
27 1. The mortgage originator; and
28 2. The mortgage lender; and
29 (ii) An affidavit stating:
30 1. The date on which the default occurred and the nature of
31 the default; and

SENATE BILL 242 97
1 2. If applicable, that:
2 A. A notice of intent to foreclose was sent to the mortgagor or
3 grantor in accordance with subsection (c) of this section and the date on which the notice
4 was sent; and
5 B. At the time the notice of intent to foreclose was sent, the
6 contents of the notice of intent to foreclose were accurate; and
7 (2) Be accompanied by:
8 (i) The original or a certified copy of the mortgage or deed of trust;
9 (ii) A statement of the debt remaining due and payable supported by
10 an affidavit of the plaintiff or the secured party or the agent or attorney of the plaintiff or
11 secured party;
12 (iii) A copy of the debt instrument accompanied by an affidavit
13 certifying ownership of the debt instrument;
14 (iv) If applicable, the original or a certified copy of the assignment of
15 the mortgage for purposes of foreclosure or the deed of appointment of a substitute trustee;
16 (v) If any defendant is an individual, an affidavit that is in
17 compliance with [§ 521] § 3931 of the Servicemembers Civil Relief Act[, 50 U.S.C. App. §
18 501 et seq.];
19 (vi) If applicable, a copy of the notice of intent to foreclose;
20 (vii) If the secured party and mortgagor or grantor have elected to
21 participate in prefile mediation, the report of the prefile mediation issued by the Office of
22 Administrative Hearings;
23 (viii) If the secured party and the mortgagor or grantor have not
24 elected to participate in prefile mediation, a statement that the parties have not elected to
25 participate in prefile mediation;
26 (ix) In addition to any other filing fees required by law, a filing fee in
27 the amount of $450; and
28 (x) 1. If the loss mitigation analysis has been completed subject
29 to subsection (g) of this section, a final loss mitigation affidavit in the form prescribed by
30 regulation adopted by the Commissioner of Financial Regulation; and

98 SENATE BILL 242
1 2. If the loss mitigation analysis has not been completed, a
2 preliminary loss mitigation affidavit in the form prescribed by regulation adopted by the
3 Commissioner of Financial Regulation.
